section.section:
"Regulated activity" means any of the following activities in a nontidal wetland or within a 25 foot buffer of the nontidal wetland:
The removal, excavation, or dredging of soil, sand, gravel, minerals, organic matter, or materials of any kind;
The changing of existing drainage characteristics, sedimentation patterns, flow patterns, or flood retention characteristics;
The disturbance of the water level or water table by drainage, impoundment, or other means;
The dumping, discharging of material, or filling with material, including the driving of piles and placing of obstructions;
The grading or removal of material that would alter existing topography; and
The destruction or removal of plant life that would alter the character of a nontidal wetland.
